Later, several more attempts were made on O'Donnell using various firearms, but each time he miraculously remained safe and sound [46]. On February 14, 1929, the well-known massacre in the underworld on St. his men to get rid of Bugs Moran's rival gang. Four of his men arrived at the garage at 2122 North Clark Street[47][48]: two of them were dressed in police uniforms, the other two were in business suits and coats. Armed with pistols -Thompson machine guns, these four seized seven people from the Moran gang and disarmed them, allegedly for a search, after which they shot all seven.